	(text "EN-Pin:\nThe LSF family has an EN input that is used to disable the device by setting EN LOW,\nplacing all I/Os in the high-impedance state.\nSince the LSF family of devices are switch-type voltage translators,\nthe power consumption is very low.\nTI recommends always enabling the LSF family for bidirectional applications (I2C)\n\nThe 200kΩ, bias resistor is required to allow Vref_B to regulate the EN input and properly bias the \ndevice for translation."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 148.59 -28.956 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "e9eea0df-7e4e-4497-b36e-df95ee51a541")
	)
